My Favorite Idea

Borrow the construction rules, not the alphabet.

Instead of inventing dozens of arbitrary symbols, define a tiny grammar.

For example:

○ = persistent state
△ = transformation
□ = boundary
↑ = propagation
• = seed
≈ = relation

Then

○↑

means

“state propagates”

while

△○

means

“transformation stabilizes”

and

□≈○

means

“boundary defines a state through relation.”

Now the symbols are readable once you know the grammar, much like algebra or circuit diagrams.

